description:
&lt;p&gt;There is an exciting career opportunity for a highly motivated and suitably experienced nurse to join the team of Cancer Clinical Nurse Specialist at Guys and St Thomas&#39; Hospital within the Gynae-oncology services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gynae-Oncology is part of the Cancer and Surgery Strategic Business unit (SBU) with an aim of bringing excellent, high-quality care to patients with their Cancer journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to have a knowledge of cancer pathways, gynaecology experience and a passion to holistically support patients from the moment of diagnosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CNS team work closely with the medical team and other healthcare professional to ensure patients receive the best care possible. A high level of communications skills are key to being successful in this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate with enjoy and have the ability to work within a small team and autonomously when needed., especially in nurse-led clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants with a key interest in cancer, women&#39;s services and supporting patients and pathways are invited to apply for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020 (midnight)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 23rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bhav Gadher - Surgical Oncology Matron - bhavisha.gadher1@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;June Allen - Head of Nursing - june.allen@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
